SIMPLE: trepang
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trepang
<hw>Tre*pang"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay
<ets>tr⟦imac⟧pang</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
several species of large holothurians, some of which are dried and
extensively used as food in China; -- called also <altname>b⟦ecir⟧che de
mer</altname>, <altname>sea cucumber</altname>, and <altname>sea
slug</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tripang</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The edible trepangs are mostly large species of
<gen>Holothuria</gen>, especially <spn>Holothuria edulis</spn>. They are
taken in vast quantities in the <geog>East Indies</geog>, where they are
dried and smoked, and then shipped to <country>China</country>. They are
used as an ingredient in certain kinds of soup.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trepanize</ent>⟦br⟧
